values: 题目，主题；话题，问题；学科，科目；主语
To subject is to cause or force someone or something to experience something harmful or unpleasant.
To subject someone to something means to force them to do or experience it.
The location of the trees will subject them to strong winds from the hurricane.
The officers subjected everyone to a careful search before they left the plane.
